=head1 DESCRIPTION

An object that defines the email template to use for an email message,
and the values to use for any message variables in that template. An
I<email template> is a type of message template that contains content
that you want to reuse in email messages that you send. You can
specifiy the email template by providing the name or ARN of an I<email
template> previously saved in your Amazon SES account or by providing
the full template content.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 Attachments => ArrayRef[L<Paws::SESv2::Attachment>]

The List of attachments to include in your email. All recipients will
receive the same attachments.


=head2 Headers => ArrayRef[L<Paws::SESv2::MessageHeader>]

The list of message headers that will be added to the email message.


=head2 TemplateArn => Str

The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the template.


=head2 TemplateContent => L<Paws::SESv2::EmailTemplateContent>

The content of the template.

Amazon SES supports only simple substitions when you send email using
the C<SendEmail> or C<SendBulkEmail> operations and you provide the
full template content in the request.


=head2 TemplateData => Str

An object that defines the values to use for message variables in the
template. This object is a set of key-value pairs. Each key defines a
message variable in the template. The corresponding value defines the
value to use for that variable.


=head2 TemplateName => Str

The name of the template. You will refer to this name when you send
email using the C<SendTemplatedEmail> or C<SendBulkTemplatedEmail>
operations.



